<paragraph id="AA425C2ABF2DFF915A47FC16306C4FE8" blockId="64.[264,1323,969,1316]" pageId="64" pageNumber="65">
<emphasis id="98898038BF2DFF915A47FC16372D4F67" bold="true" box="[312,579,1009,1035]" pageId="64" pageNumber="65">General distribution:</emphasis>
This is a boreal species occurring across North America from Newfoundland, Labrador, and northern New 
<collectingCountry id="D2EA1CBABF2DFF915841FBFD36CE4F58" box="[830,928,1050,1076]" name="United Kingdom" pageId="64" pageNumber="65">England</collectingCountry>
west to central Yukon, British Columbia, and Washington. There are several disjunct populations, including GSMNP, the Rocky Mountains in Colorado, and a coastal bog in central Oregon. (
<bibRefCitation id="CE6C21DBBF2DFF915F51FB8D319B4FE8" author="Lafontaine, J. D." box="[1070,1269,1130,1156]" pageId="64" pageNumber="65" refId="ref23206" refString="Lafontaine, J. D. (1998) Noctuoidea, Noctuidae (part): Noctuinae, Noctuini. In: Hodges, R. W., Davis, D. R., Dominick, T., Ferguson, D. C., Munroe, E. G., &amp; Powell, J. A. (Eds.), The Moths of America North of Mexico, fasc. 25.3, Allen Press, Lawrence, Kansas. 348 pp." type="book" year="1998">Lafontaine 1998</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="AA425C2ABF2DFF915A47FB76348A4E48" blockId="64.[264,1323,969,1316]" pageId="64" pageNumber="65">
<emphasis id="98898038BF2DFF915A47FB76348E4FC7" bold="true" box="[312,480,1169,1195]" pageId="64" pageNumber="65">Larval hosts:</emphasis>
Larvae are spruce­fir feeders reared on white and Englemann spruce (
<taxonomicName id="6DFD27A9BF2DFF915A6DFB5D37114FB8" authority="(Moench) Voss" authorityName="Voss" authorityYear="2010" baseAuthorityName="Moench" box="[274,639,1210,1236]" class="Pinopsida" family="Pinaceae" genus="Picea" kingdom="Plantae" order="Pinales" pageId="64" pageNumber="65" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="glauca">
<emphasis id="98898038BF2DFF915A6DFB5D34DA4FBF" box="[274,436,1210,1235]" italics="true" pageId="64" pageNumber="65">Picea glauca</emphasis>
(Moench) Voss
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="6DFD27A9BF2DFF9159B4FB5D36A54FB8" authority="Parry" authorityName="Parry" box="[715,971,1210,1236]" class="Pinopsida" family="Pinaceae" genus="Picea" kingdom="Plantae" order="Pinales" pageId="64" pageNumber="65" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="englemanni">
<emphasis id="98898038BF2DFF9159B4FB5D36174FBF" box="[715,889,1210,1235]" italics="true" pageId="64" pageNumber="65">P. englemanni</emphasis>
Parry
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="6DFD27A9BF2DFF9158A0FB5D31274FB8" box="[991,1097,1210,1236]" class="Pinopsida" family="Pinaceae" kingdom="Plantae" order="Pinales" pageId="64" pageNumber="65" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="family">Pinaceae</taxonomicName>
) and balsam and subalpine fir (
<taxonomicName id="6DFD27A9BF2DFF915AC3FB0537124F97" box="[444,636,1250,1275]" class="Pinopsida" family="Pinaceae" genus="Abies" kingdom="Plantae" order="Pinales" pageId="64" pageNumber="65" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="balsamea">
<emphasis id="98898038BF2DFF915AC3FB0537124F97" box="[444,636,1250,1275]" italics="true" pageId="64" pageNumber="65">Abies balsamea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(L.) Mill. and 
<taxonomicName id="6DFD27A9BF2DFF915837FB0531C84F90" authority="(Hook.) Nutt." authorityName="Nutt." baseAuthorityName="Hook." box="[840,1190,1250,1276]" class="Pinopsida" family="Pinaceae" genus="Abies" kingdom="Plantae" order="Pinales" pageId="64" pageNumber="65" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="lasiocarpa">
<emphasis id="98898038BF2DFF915837FB0536834F97" box="[840,1005,1250,1275]" italics="true" pageId="64" pageNumber="65">A. lasiocarpa</emphasis>
(Hook.) Nutt.
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="6DFD27A9BF2DFF915FC6FB05304D4F90" box="[1209,1315,1250,1276]" class="Pinopsida" family="Pinaceae" kingdom="Plantae" order="Pinales" pageId="64" pageNumber="65" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="family">Pinaceae</taxonomicName>
) (
<bibRefCitation id="CE6C21DBBF2DFF915A6FFAED34B94E48" author="Lafontaine, J. D." box="[272,471,1290,1316]" pageId="64" pageNumber="65" refId="ref23206" refString="Lafontaine, J. D. (1998) Noctuoidea, Noctuidae (part): Noctuinae, Noctuini. In: Hodges, R. W., Davis, D. R., Dominick, T., Ferguson, D. C., Munroe, E. G., &amp; Powell, J. A. (Eds.), The Moths of America North of Mexico, fasc. 25.3, Allen Press, Lawrence, Kansas. 348 pp." type="book" year="1998">Lafontaine 1998</bibRefCitation>
